  "texts": [
    "The approach assumes that the real-time application's tasks are known and that the source code is available.",
    "By analyzing the source code, the method associates each execution path with an execution time and the probability of taking that path.",
    "The proposed method constructs a tree-based representation of the source code, recursively applying formulas to each node to determine execution times and conditions for each path.",
    "Probabilistic evaluation is then performed on these conditions, taking into account the independence of external random variables.",
    "The method does not consider hardware-specific details and assumes constant, context-independent instruction execution times."
  ],
